Please try the following Troubleshoot Steps if ink cartridges are not recognized or do not work upon first installation: The contact between the ink cartridge and the printer must be clean for proper functioning. (If any dirt, ink or paper dust is on the contacts, the printer may indicate that the ink cartridge is bad. ) To ensure a clean contact, follow the steps below: Use a pencil eraser (preferably rubber) and firmly rub over the contacts, then gently brush away any debris. Re-install the cartridge into the printer (You may have to take it out and reinstall it 2-3 times). If the problem persists, reset your printer by: 1. Turning off the printer with the cartridges installed. 2. Unplug printer and leave everything off for 2 minutes. 3. Turn on printer and attempt to print again.
